quran[8]{c,v,t,f}:
  16,80,"And Allah has made for you, of your houses,<i class=""s"">(places of) </i>rest and has assigned for you out of the skins of livestock<i class=""s"">(portable) </i>homes which you find light on the day you travel and on the day you encamp and, from their wool and fur and hair, furnishings and an enjoyment for a while."
  16,81,"And Allah has made for you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a> shades out of what He created, and has made for you shelters of the mountains, and has made for you garments to protect you from the heat and garments to protect you from your violence; thus He completes His blessings upon you, that you may submit."
  16,82,"So if they{1}turn away, then certainly your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>only duty is evident proclamation.",footnotes:1:A grammatical shift from 2nd person to 3rd person.
  16,83,"They recognize Allah’s blessing then they deny it, as most of them are the deniers."
  16,84,"And on the day when We raise up a witness from every community —then those who denied are not permitted, nor are they allowed to make amends."
  16,85,"And when those who did injustice see the punishment,<i class=""s"">(they will realize that) </i>never shall it be lightened for them, nor shall they be given respite."
  16,86,"And when the ones who associated<i class=""s"">(others with God) </i>see their associates{1}, they will say, “Our Lord, these are our associates whom we used to call upon apart from You.” So they cast{2}to them the statement, “Very truly, you are liars.”",footnotes:1:The false gods.Frequently the Qur’an addresses the events of the Hereafter in pasttense; this grammatical shift should be pondered by the reader.
  16,87,"And they cast forth to Allah, on that day,<i class=""s"">(their) </i>submissiveness, and whatever they used to fabricate strayed away from them."
